Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). In a large bowl, mix together the peanut butter, butter, vanilla, and eggs (optional). In another bowl, mix together the sugar, brown sugar, flour, cocoa, and baking soda. Pour the dry ingredients into large bowl and mix together. Fold the chocolate chips into the batter. Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheets. Bake for 10 minutes. Enjoy!!!